===Etymology===
German [[Marzipan]], earlier [[marcipan]], a misinterpretation of Italian [[marzapane]] (as if from Latin [[Marci]] [[panis]] ‘Mark's bread’), now thought orignally to come from [[w:Martaban|Martaban]], a Burmese port known for its spice exports.

===Noun===
'''marzipan'''
# a [[confection]] of [[almond]] [[paste]], [[sugar]] and [[egg white]]

